<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870723-0163 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News:Calny's President, Taylor,Gets Added Post of Chief</HL><DD> 07/23/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> WNEWS CLNY </IN><DATELINE> SAN MATEO, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Calny Inc. named its president, M. Hal Taylor, to the additional post of chief executive officer of the restaurant franchisee.    As chief executive, Mr. Taylor, 47 years old, succeeds Martin T. Hart, who remains chairman. Mr. Hart, 51, assumed both the president and chief executive posts on an interim basis after Calny fired Robert T. Larive in November.    Mr. Taylor joined Calny in January and was named president in April. </TEXT></DOC>